text: Agdistis adenensis is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Yemen, Oman, Iran and Bahrain.A new species, a new synonym, and new distribution records in the genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 from Iran (Pterophoridae: Agdistinae) ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths of the Arabian Peninsula Category:Moths of Western Asia Category:Taxa named by Hans Georg Amsel Category:Moths described in 1961
